
---


@startuml

' Entities
class Contract {
    +id: String
    +startDate: Date
    +endDate: Date
    +deliveryConditions: String
    +legalTerms: String
}

class Acquisition {
    +id: String
    +model: String
    +price: Double
    +customizations: List<String>
    +deliveryDate: Date
}

class Aircraft {
    +serialNumber: String
    +model: String
    +status: String (e.g., "built", "in-production")
}

class AirlineCompany {
    +name: String
    +country: String
    +isMainCompany: Boolean
}

class Salesperson {
    +id: String
    +name: String
    +department: String
}

class CompanyRelationship {
    +parentId: String
    +childId: String
    +relationshipType: String (e.g., "mother-daughter")
}

' Relationships
Contract "1" -- "0..*" Acquisition : contains
Contract "1" -- "1" Salesperson : managed by
Acquisition "1" -- "1" Aircraft : builds
AirlineCompany "1" -- "0..*" Acquisition : purchases
AirlineCompany "1" -- "0..*" CompanyRelationship : has relationship
AirlineCompany "1" -- "0..*" AirlineCompany : related to (via CompanyRelationship)

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Contract`**: A high-level agreement between Boeing and an airline company. Contains shared terms.
- **`Acquisition`**: Represents the purchase of a specific aircraft under a contract. Has unique details like model, price, delivery date.
- **`Aircraft`**: The actual plane being built or delivered.
- **`AirlineCompany`**: The buyer. Can have multiple acquisitions and can be part of a parent/child relationship.
- **`Salesperson`**: Manages contracts; one person may manage multiple contracts.
- **`CompanyRelationship`**: Tracks mother-daughter or partner relationships between airlines.

